Cardiovascular System

Objectives

1. Heart, arteries, capillaries, veins, lymphatic vascular system  
2. Functions: distributes hormones, nutrients, transports waste products to excretory organs  
3. Along with nervous system: integrates function of organism  
4. Lecture Objectives:  
    + General features shared by all vessels  
    + Changes in these general features as arteries/veins change size  
    + How to distinguish arteries, veins & lymphatics in tissue sections  
    + Blood supply and innervation/signaling of the vasculature  
    + Different capillary types: structure/function/location in the body  
    + Control of blood flow through a capillary bed  
    + Control of vascular growth - clinical correlation

